      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;span-and-linear-independence&#34;&gt;Span and Linear Independence&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-1&#34;&gt;Exercise 1&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suppose $v_1, v_2, v_3, v_4$ spans $V$. Prove that the list&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
$$v_1 - v_2, v_2 - v_3, v_3 - v_4, v_4$$&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
also spans $V$.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;exercise-2&#34;&gt;Exercise 2&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify the assertions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A list $v$ of one vector $v \in V$ is linearly independent if and only if $v \neq 0$.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A list of two vectors in $V$ is linearly independent if and only if neither vector is a scalar multiple of the other.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
